Best Glamping Spots in the United States - Under Canvas®
  URL: https://www.undercanvas.com/blog/best-glamping-spots-in-the-united-states/
  Explore the best glamping spots in the United States, from luxury tents to safari-style stays in national parks and scenic regions.

  --- Content ---
  Search for:Go
  
  
  
  Camping, Glamping, Travel Tips \|
  
  
  May 2, 2025
  
  
  
  If you’re dreaming of sleeping under the stars without sacrificing comfort, Under Canvas brings you the best of both worlds—luxury safari-inspired tents set in some of America’s most extraordinary landscapes. Think: a king-size bed beneath a starry sky, ensuite bathrooms with hot showers, locally sourced cuisine, and daily adventures that connect you to the wild beauty around you. From red rock deserts to forested hideaways and coastal cliffs, here’s where you can unplug and reconnect with the great outdoors—all while “roughing it” in style.
  
  ## Glamping at Under Canvas
  
  At Under Canvas, glamping means waking up to birdsong instead of alarms and ending your day by a crackling fire under a sky full of stars. It’s sinking into a real bed after hiking, sipping premium coffee on your private deck, and enjoying s’mores with loved ones. Safari-inspired tents come fully outfitted with [hotel-worthy amenities](https://www.undercanvas.com/blog/hotel-amenities-at-a-luxury-outdoor-resort/)—so you can pack light and settle in. We partner with top-rated local guides to curate unforgettable adventures, and just when you thought it couldn’t get any better, every location is [dog-friendly](https://www.undercanvas.com/blog/dog-packing-list/)—so your four-legged explorer is welcome, too.
  
  ## Acadia National Park, Maine
  
  Wake up to the scent of salt air at [Under Canvas Acadia](https://www.undercanvas.com/camps/acadia), where your private deck overlooks Maine’s wild coastline. Spend the day hiking Acadia’s granite peaks, exploring tidepools, and cycling the scenic carriage roads. After wandering around charming Bar Harbor, return to camp for a locally-inspired lobster boil dinner and cozy up in your safari tent with a waterfront breeze and the soft glow of your in-tent wood stove. The next morning, catch the first sunrise in the U.S. from nearby Cadillac Mountain.
  
  ## Bryce Canyon National Park, Utah
  
  Set at a refreshing high elevation, [Under Canvas Bryce Canyon](https://www.undercanvas.com/camps/bryce-canyon/) places you right in the heart of red rock country, with cooler temperatures perfect for desert adventures. Wander among Bryce’s otherworldly hoodoos, take a guided horseback ride through pine forests, then return for fireside cocktails and s’mores under one of the darkest, starriest skies in America. Tents feature king beds, ensuite bathrooms, and West Elm furnishings—blending rugged beauty with total relaxation.
  
  ## Columbia River Gorge, Washington
  
  At [Under Canvas Columbia River Gorge](https://www.undercanvas.com/camps/columbia-river-gorge/), your day begins with mountain views and ends with fireside stargazing. Take a scenic drive along the Historic Columbia River Highway, hike trails along the Waterfall Corridor, or sip local vintages at nearby vineyards. Join a farm-to-table cooking class led by a private chef, then recharge at local cafés with artisan coffee. Back at camp, dine al fresco or gather around for stargazing at the outdoor lounge area, or opt for a Stargazer Tent, complete with a viewing window above your bed to drift off beneath the stars.
  
  ## Grand Canyon National Park, Arizona
  
  Just 25 minutes from the [South Rim](https://www.undercanvas.com/blog/top-14-views-from-the-grand-canyons-south-rim/) entrance of Grand Canyon National Park, [Under Canvas Grand Canyon](https://www.undercanvas.com/camps/grand-canyon/) blends rustic charm with upscale touches, including organic bath products, wood-burning stoves for chilly desert nights, and yoga sessions set amidst 160 acres of piñon and juniper forest. Spend your day hiking the canyon rim or rafting the Colorado River, then gather around the fire pit to swap stories from the day and watch the sky ignite with stars in this Dark Sky-certified resort destination. There’s no better place to base your Grand Canyon adventure.
  
  ## Glacier National Park, Montana
  
  Experience Big Sky Country at its most spectacular. Just seven miles from Glacier’s west entrance, [Under Canvas Glacier](https://www.undercanvas.com/camps/glacier/) is your home base for kayaking glacier-fed lakes, hiking alpine trails, exploring wildflower-filled meadows, and driving the famous [Going-to-the-Sun Road](https://www.undercanvas.com/blog/driving-going-to-the-sun-road-do-i-need-a-reservation/). After a day of adventure, enjoy local Montana cuisine in the open-air lobby, sip a glass of wine by the fire pit, bite into gooey s’mores, and fall asleep to the sound of swaying pines—all while staying cozy in a king bed wrapped in plush linens.
  
  ## Great Smoky Mountains, Tennessee
  
  Just 10 minutes from Gatlinburg and the Great Smoky Mountains National Park entrance, [Under Canvas Great Smoky Mountains](https://www.undercanvas.com/camps/great-smoky-mountains/) invites you to immerse yourself in the “Land of Blue Smoke,” set on 182 acres of lush, wooded terrain. Wake to misty mountain vistas, raft the Pigeon River, explore trails and waterfalls, then visit nearby [Gatlinburg and Pigeon Forge](https://www.undercanvas.com/blog/gatlinburg-vs-pigeon-forge-great-smoky-mountains-gateway-cities/). Return for Southern-inspired meals and acoustic music under twinkling string lights. Safari-inspired tents feature private decks, ensuite bathrooms, and the perfect mix of rustic and refined for cozy mountain nights.
  
  ## Lake Powell-Grand Staircase, Utah
  
  At [Under Canvas Lake Powell-Grand Staircase](https://www.undercanvas.com/camps/lake-powell/), adventure is at your doorstep. Paddleboard across Lake Powell, explore hidden slot canyons—including one right on-site—and take in sweeping views from the camp’s canyon rim setting. After boating Lake Powell, sunbathing at Lone Rock Beach, catching the sunset at Horseshoe Bend, or exploring nearby Grand Staircase-Escalante—or whatever floats your boat—return to plush beds, hot showers, and nightly campfires beneath a desert sky that puts on a show only the American Southwest can deliver.
  
  ## Moab, Utah
  
  Two national parks—Arches and Canyonlands—are short drives from [Under Canvas Moab](https://www.undercanvas.com/camps/moab/), where luxury tents await in a red rock wonderland. Off-road on slickrock trails, raft the Colorado River, or climb towering red cliffs by day. Take scenic pictures of arches. Then retreat to camp for shaded lounge spaces, camp programming, and epic desert sunsets you’ll never forget. Stick around for a spectacular cosmic show at this DarkSky-certified resort in Utah’s Canyon Country.
  
  ## Mount Rushmore, South Dakota
  
  Nestled on a historic gold mining settlement, [Under Canvas Mount Rushmore](https://www.undercanvas.com/camps/mount-rushmore) combines Black Hills adventure with upscale comforts. Explore Mount Rushmore and watch the [lighting ceremony](https://www.undercanvas.com/blog/mount-rushmore-lighting-ceremony-all-you-need-to-know/) for a sense of American history and pride, hike Custer State Park’s scenic trails, visit the Crazy Horse Memorial, then unwind with views of the illuminated monument from camp. Spacious safari-inspired tents and a peaceful, forested setting create a perfect South Dakota escape. As night falls, relax under starry skies for a rewarding end to your day.
  
  ## North Yellowstone-Paradise Valley, Montana
  
  With wild rivers and wide-open spaces, [Under Canvas North Yellowstone-Paradise Valley](https://www.undercanvas.com/camps/north-yellowstone/) is, well, paradise for nature lovers. Located on a mile-long stretch of the Yellowstone River, this camp brings Montana’s legendary beauty to your private accommodations. Float, fish, or swim steps from your tent, then venture into Yellowstone’s Lamar Valley – America’s Serengeti – to spot wolves, bears, and the famous bison herds. Evenings mean Montana-smoked meats, campfire moments, and a big sky filled with stars.
  
  ## West Yellowstone, Montana
  
  Geysers, grizzlies, and grand adventures await. Stay nearby Yellowstone’s west entrance at [Under Canvas West Yellowstone](https://www.undercanvas.com/camps/west-yellowstone/), where safari-inspired tents, ensuite bathrooms, and upscale dining elevate your national park getaway. Spend your days visiting Old Faithful, Grand Prismatic Spring, and Mammoth Hot Springs—then swap stories by the fire under Montana’s famously wide-open skies, just 10 minutes from America’s first national park for a one-of-a-kind glamping experience.
  
  Pro Tip: Explore the best of Yellowstone with a stay near both park entrances. Check out our [guide to Yellowstone Entrances](https://www.undercanvas.com/blog/guide-to-yellowstone-entrances/) for how to make the most of your visit.
  
  ## Yosemite National Park, California
  
  Steps from a park shuttle stop, [Under Canvas Yosemite](https://www.undercanvas.com/camps/yosemite/) pairs convenience with upscale comfort for experiencing the park’s magic. Wander postcard-perfect Yosemite Valley, chase waterfalls, hike the park’s many trails, picnic beneath ancient sequoias, and take a wild swim in an alpine lake framed by mountains. The possibilities are nearly endless. Back at camp, sip cocktails, local wines, and beers at the outdoor lounge, cozy up by the fire, and sleep in a plush bed under a sky bursting with stars.
  
  ## Zion National Park, Utah
  
  Defined by dramatic cliffs and river canyons, Zion is a place of awe, and [Under Canvas Zion](https://www.undercanvas.com/camps/zion/) reflects that. Just 20 miles from the park entrance, this camp offers proximity to iconic hikes like The Narrows and Angels Landing, as well as world-class slickrock mountain biking trails and [via ferrata](https://www.undercanvas.com/blog/zion-via-ferrata-what-is-it-and-why-you-should-do-it/) routes. After a day of exploration, dine on delicious locally-inspired meals, stretch out with sunset yoga, and enjoy a nightcap of s’mores around the fire under Utah’s desert skies.
  
  ## Plan Your Glamping Stay with Under Canvas
  
  At Under Canvas, every detail brings you closer to nature without compromising on comfort. Wake to golden light in your safari-inspired tent, then spend the day hiking scenic trails, paddling rivers, or simply soaking in the views. Back at camp, unwind with chef-prepared [dining](https://www.undercanvas.com/experiences/culinary/), private decks, hot showers, and cozy indoor and outdoor spaces. Enjoy open-air yoga, live acoustic music, and hands-on crafts. As stars fill the sky, gather for nightly s’mores before drifting off in your plush king bed – opt for the [Stargazer Tent](https://www.undercanvas.com/tents/), featuring a viewing window above the bed for a truly unforgettable glamping stay. Here, luxury and wilderness come together for an adventure like no other.
  
  [BOOK YOUR STAY](https://www.undercanvas.com/camps/)
  
  Discover more unique nature-based stays throughout the US in our [Outdoor Collection](https://www.undercanvas.com/outdoor-collection/).
  
