World's 10 Top Glamping Destinations - Zicasso
  URL: https://www.zicasso.com/a/ac/glamping/ms
  World's 10 Top Glamping Destinations ; 1. Patagonia, Chile. Glamping dome interior at EcoCamp Patagonia in Torres del Paine, Chile ; 2. Uluru, Australia.

  --- Content ---
  ![](data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg%20height='811.9916666666666'%20width='1251'%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20version='1.1'%3E%3C/svg%3E)
  
  ![Glamping at EcoCamp Patagonia in Torres del Paine, Chile](https://www.zicasso.com/static/0be5fabd37aa0e0b071b1653130b9f67/7d056/0be5fabd37aa0e0b071b1653130b9f67.jpg)
  
  Photo courtesy of EcoLodge Patagonia
  
  From unbridled panoramas of remote mountains to spectacular views of wildlife grazing, our 10 best glamping destinations demonstrate an unrivaled mix of luxury and natural beauty.
  
  Find breathtaking views of an Australian monolith as it changes colors at dawn. Embrace nature at a reflective lake in the remote mountains of Laos. Search for tigers in India, listen for wandering elephants in sub-Saharan Africa, or lounge under the desert sky in Morocco.
  
  Glamping combines the effortless with the unexpected, creating surprising moments in nature and offering comfortable and glamorous accommodations you can experience with our list of top glamping destinations.
  
  ![Glamping dome interior at  EcoCamp Patagonia in Torres del Paine, Chile](https://res.cloudinary.com/zicasso/image/fetch/c_fill,w_1024/e_sharpen:60/q_auto/dpr_auto/f_auto/https://images.zicasso.com/04938e39600c2de716ec4cc573b9e099.jpg)Photo courtesy of EcoLodge Patagonia
  
  Patagonia is famous for its untamed wilderness, where dramatic nature becomes a window from which to view the world. Glamping in Patagonia combines the comforts of a luxury hotel with the beauty of the outside world, removing the barriers of resort grounds or glass facades for a more captivating experience.
  
  Create the most exciting moments for you with our [Patagonia Travel Guide](https://www.zicasso.com/g/patagonia) to explore more opportunities in which you can embrace lush vegetation and unparalleled views of glacial lakes, or relax in the wild surrounded by jagged mountain peaks covered in snow or high-altitude plains supporting grazing vicuna. Find more ideas for exploring the region at your pace with [Our 7 Best Patagonia Itineraries](https://www.zicasso.com/a/patagonia/best-itineraries).
  
  **Highlights:** Torres del Paine National Park • Horseback riding • Glaciers • Trekking • Glacial lakes
  
  **Recommended length of stay:** 3-4 days
  
  **Learn more:** [Chile Tours & Vacations](https://www.zicasso.com/l/latin-america/chile/h) • [Patagonia Tours & Vacations](https://www.zicasso.com/l/latin-america/patagonia/h)
  
  Back to Top
  
  ![Longitude 131 resort with view to Uluru at Uluṟu-Kata Tjuṯa National Park, Australia](https://res.cloudinary.com/zicasso/image/fetch/c_fill,w_1024/e_sharpen:60/q_auto/dpr_auto/f_auto/https://images.zicasso.com/1fea92d769fa862b9f0bc9e415d32e16.jpg)Photo courtesy of Longitude 131
  
  Luxury, culture, and history converge at Uluru. Glamping in Australia’s Outback can feel like the ultimate adventure, where the sands glow orange, the monolith changes colors with the shifting daylight, and wildlife rustles the sparse brush for exciting moments during an [Australia vacation & tour](https://www.zicasso.com/l/south-pacific/australia/h).
  
  Home to one of the oldest cultures in the world, the stories reflect the wonders of nature stretching across the scenery and into the sky, demonstrating the deep-rooted connection of the local community with the landscape and wildlife, as well as the fantasy of unfettered views of the night sky and untamed wilderness.
  
  **Highlights:** Uluru • Kata-Tjuta • Wildlife • Camel trains • Aerial tours • Walking tours • Cultural center
  
  **Recommended length of stay:** 1-2 days
  
  **Learn more:** [Australia Travel Guide](https://www.zicasso.com/g/australia)
  
  Back to Top![Hilltop tent with a view at Rosewood Luang Prabang](https://res.cloudinary.com/zicasso/image/fetch/c_fill,w_1024/e_sharpen:60/q_auto/dpr_auto/f_auto/https://images.zicasso.com/bfa8ff06c70ff024c6feff7965a7539a.jpg)Photo courtesy of Rosewood Luang, Prabang
  
  Laos often feels like one of the world’s best-kept secrets and glamping in the mountains around Luang Prabang opens visitors’ eyes to its culture, heritage, and scenery. Witness the Nam Khan river meet the mighty Mekong. Explore an ancient capital brimming with historic temples. Wander along trails weaving through misty mountains to find waterfalls plunging into welcoming pools.
  
  Glamping in Luang Prabang provides sensational views and connects to local communities favoring farming and permaculture, demonstrating best-practice sustainability. With active adventures, connections to local artisans, and panoramic views radiating from the grounds, glamping in Laos is a welcome surprise, especially when combined with other such destinations during a [Southeast Asia tour & vacation](https://www.zicasso.com/l/asia/southeast/h).
  
  **Highlights:** Phousi Mountain • Wat Monorom • Kuang Si Waterfalls • Wat Xieng Thong • Trekking
  
  **Recommended length of stay:** 2-3 days
  
  **Learn more:** [Laos Tours](https://www.zicasso.com/l/asia/laos/h)
  
  Back to Top![Lak Tented Camp on Lak Lake in Daklak Province, Vietnam](https://res.cloudinary.com/zicasso/image/fetch/c_fill,w_1024/e_sharpen:60/q_auto/dpr_auto/f_auto/https://images.zicasso.com/014d0801e7f405835ceff62ab9fc620f.jpg)Photo courtesy of Lak Tented Camp (@laktentedcamp)
  
  When each glamping destination focuses on blending natural beauty with luxury, few places surpass expectations like Vietnam’s Daklak Province. Overlooking the reflective waters of a calm lake, visiting the province can feel exotic, secluded, and opulent. It brings visitors close to nature, while also celebrating local culture with experiences that can connect with the [best places to visit in Vietnam](https://www.zicasso.com/a/vietnam/ms).
  
  Surround yourself with the sounds of nature beneath the star-studded night sky or enjoy activities that keep you active throughout the day, among them kayaking over the lake or trekking through the rolling hillside. Daklak province is mastering glamping by providing resort experiences with immersive, natural beauty, using sustainable practices.
  
  **Highlights:** Dray Sap Falls • Lak Lake • Ethnographic Museum • Trekking • Kayaking • Dray Nur Falls
  
  **Recommended length of stay:** 2-3 days
  
  **Learn more:** [Vietnam Tours & Vacations](https://www.zicasso.com/l/asia/vietnam/h) • [Vietnam Travel Guide](https://www.zicasso.com/g/vietnam)
  
  Back to Top![Kayakers on Prek Tachan river next to Cardamom Tented Camp in Koh Kong Province, Cambodia](https://res.cloudinary.com/zicasso/image/fetch/c_fill,w_1024/e_sharpen:60/q_auto/dpr_auto/f_auto/https://images.zicasso.com/7dad6566eaa3c9006afbccef398b3e50.jpg)Photo courtesy of Cardamom Tented Camp
  
  Glamping offers unique properties that often take advantage of nature’s wonders and those in Cambodia’s Koh Kong Province exemplify the practice.
  
  Far beyond a tent in the wilderness, Cambodia’s glamping expands your perspective on the diverse and creative ways in which you can open accommodations to the brilliance of the natural world for enchanting encounters that highlight some of the [top things to do in Cambodia](https://www.zicasso.com/a/cambodia/td).
  
  Participate in protecting wildlife by helping patrols defend gibbons and macaques, kayak or hike to explore the jungle terrain, embrace a scenic boat ride, or witness unique birdlife to discover more of the bountiful nature that thrives in the province.
  
  **Highlights:** Koh Moul island • Tatai Waterfall • Lam Da Beach • Veal Achaut Waterfall • Trekking • Koh Kong island
  
  **Recommended length of stay:** 2-3 days
  
  **Learn more:** [Cambodia Tours & Vacations](https://www.zicasso.com/l/asia/cambodia/h)
  
  Back to Top
  
  ![Aman i Khas tented resort in near Ranthambore National Park, India](https://res.cloudinary.com/zicasso/image/fetch/c_fill,w_1024/e_sharpen:60/q_auto/dpr_auto/f_auto/https://images.zicasso.com/387124708807d352b5b00d51514c1e03.jpg)Photo courtesy of Aman i Khas, an Aman Resort
  
  Glamping in Ranthambore National Park embodies opulence, rivaling regional palace accommodations by combining luxury and nature. Rugged beauty can feel indulgent as you uncover the civil and natural history of the protected area, while embracing the majestic backdrop of ruined pavilions, ancient temples, and soaring jungle canopy.
  
  Searching for traces of the elusive tiger crowns the marvels of the area and provides unique opportunities for wildlife spotting unlike anywhere in the world. When glamping in Ranthambore National Park, it can feel as though you’ve stepped back in time. Explore new ideas to enjoy during your trip with our [top 8 things to do in India](https://www.zicasso.com/a/india/td).
  
  **Highlights:** Ranthambore Fort • Tiger safari • Amreshwar Mahadev Temple • Surwal Lake • Padam Lake • Kachida Valley
  
  **Recommended length of stay:** 2-3 days
  
  **Learn more:** [India Tours & Vacations](https://www.zicasso.com/l/asia/india/h) • [India Travel Guide](https://www.zicasso.com/g/india)
  
  Back to Top![Luxury Duba Plains guest tent in the Okavango Delta, Botswana.](https://res.cloudinary.com/zicasso/image/fetch/c_fill,w_1024/e_sharpen:60/q_auto/dpr_auto/f_auto/https://images.zicasso.com/8bbab5f9bb8430ef431b4721e8754506.jpg)Photo courtesy Duba Plains Camp, Great Plains Conservation
  
  Glamping in the Okavango Delta gives new definitions to luxury camping and glamour. Whether rooted to a specific site or traveling in a mobile tented camp, service and opulence take the stage behind tremendous wilderness views.
  
  Total immersion into the Okavango Delta unveils fabulous viewing experiences. Open your tent to a herd of elephants wading across a waterway or listen to the songs of lively birds at dusk.
  
  When on a mobile safari, the luxury continues as you track some of the region's most elusive and sought-after wildlife for memorable sightings, whether looking for lion or leopard, wild dog or cheetah during your personalized [Okavango Delta safari](https://www.zicasso.com/l/africa/botswana/rg/okavango-delta/sa).
  
  **Highlights:** Game drives • Mokoro safari • Aerial safari • Birding
  
  **Recommended length of stay:** 4-5 days
  
  **Learn more:** [Botswana Safari Guide](https://www.zicasso.com/g/africa/botswana)
  
  Back to Top![Luxury bathroom at Singita Serengeti Sabora Tented Camp in Kenya](https://res.cloudinary.com/zicasso/image/fetch/c_fill,w_1024/e_sharpen:60/q_auto/dpr_auto/f_auto/https://images.zicasso.com/f79bf0d39d047879b82905580082826a.jpg)Photo courtesy of Singita Sabora Tented Camp
  
  The Serengeti is one of the world’s most famous safari destinations and glamping can take you miles away from other accommodations to enjoy the wilderness in the best [Serengeti safaris](https://www.zicasso.com/l/africa/tanzania/rg/serengeti/sa).
  
